race.comment: Former Godolphin galloper FLEETWOOD (1) wasn't disgraced in a richer race when resuming and is sure to have come on with that run now under the belt. Will find this assignment more to her liking and looks the one they all have to run down. GIVE GIGGLES (6) has only missed a drum once in five first-up attempts and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Respect the Gollan/Jones combination. HE'S HEAVEN (2) has placed two from two around this circuit and gets a bunch of weight off with the 3kg claim. Top-three aspirations on best form. HELL (7) loves this distance range with two wins and three placings from five starts. Include in calculations. ZOUPERB (8) strips fitter third-up from the spell and may earn some minor money.
